// Question: If ArrayList is used more frequently in enterprise applications, why should backend developers still learn LinkedList?

// Answer :

// Backend developers should learn LinkedList because it strengthens their understanding of data structures and helps them choose the right tool for different problems. Although ArrayList is used more often, LinkedList performs better when there are frequent insertions and deletions in the middle or beginning of a list. Knowledge of both data structures is commonly tested in coding interviews. Understanding their strengths and weaknesses improves problem-solving skills and helps developers write more efficient and optimized applications.